place.name: WESTWICK
place.gazetteerText: WESTWICK, a parish in Tunstead district, Norfolk; 2¾ miles S of North Walsham r. station. Post town, North Walsham, under Norwich. Acres, 1,043. Real property, £1,511. Pop., 207. Houses, 44. The manor, with W. House, belongs to J. B. Petre, Esq. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £159. Patron, J. B. Petre, Esq. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
